  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Help Sightless Tibetan Children Live Normal Lives</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Global Roots helped a sightless Tibetan woman named Kyila establish Tibet&apos;s first kindergarten boarding school for sightless children seven years ago with a cash grant of 50K. Recently, the Chinese government changed policy to allow sightless Tibetan kindergarteners to attend special government schools. This was a big victory for Kyila. Now she can concentrate on rescuing more children from home confinement and raising funds for private tutoring so that &quot;her children&quot; can go to college one day!</narrative>
  </description>
